reviews.text: I went and tried this place with my friend because of the pretty interior and the place was really nice. I love the atmosphere and it wasn't crowded at all during lunch. We could stay for quite a while in the restaurant and chatted. The food was decent. It definitely wasn't the best but I expected it because I solely came for the atmosphere. We ordered the pasta and some sort of braised beef. Both weren't bland but it's not the most outstanding food. The dessert was cheesecake, it wasn't bad but it also wasn't amazing. But food wise, although it's not excellent, it wasn't bad. One thing I didn't really like was that they don't have English set menu, which wasn't helpful at all. Being located on the 4th floor of the hotel, I think that much should be done for foreigners and tourists who stayed there. But again, maybe tourists won't eat there and would opt for better local food. There was also only one staff table runner who wasn't the friendliest but hey, it's Hong Kong although being located in a hotel and it being a western place, I would expect better.

Very nice location with calm, beautiful outdoor terrace. If I lived in the neighborhood I'd come often for the atmosphere. I ordered spaghetti and it was hearty and good, but not incredible. Mushroom soup was a bit bland. Service friendly.
Not crowded during the lunchtime at weekdays. Several choices of lunch sets. Service is good. Set lunch is a big bargain. Should give it a try.

Food ok but very bad service. Didn't feel welcomed by the staff there. Forgot some parts of the order but bill charged one more main. If u use eatigo, can't use discount for snacks and set meals. Not common for eatigo restaurants not offering discount for snacks. Have used $50 coupon for eatigo booking, but the restaurant just ignored the coupon. Definitely won't go there again.
Nice food and decor
